[base] 
[base] > query59.preql has been written and validated with `trilogy run query59.preql`. The query:
[base] > 
[base] > 1. **Imports `store_sales` twice** (as `ss1` for 2001 and `ss2` for 2002), and **merges them on `store.store_sk`** to enable cross-year pairing.
[base] > 
[base] > 2. **Defines `auto` concepts** for each day-of-week (Sunday through Saturday) for both years, summing `sales_price` (the per-unit price) grouped by `(store_sk, week_seq)`.
[base] > 
[base] > 3. **Pairs 2001 and 2002 rows** via WHERE conditions:
[base] >    - `ss1.date_dim.year = 2001`
[base] >    - `ss2.date_dim.year = 2002`
[base] >    - `ss2.date_dim.week_seq = ss1.date_dim.week_seq + 52`
[base] > 
[base] > 4. **Computes 7 day-of-week ratios** using `case` expressions that guard against zero-division (returning `null` when the 2002 denominator is zero).
[base] > 
[base] > 5. **Orders** by `store_name nulls first`, `store_id nulls first`, `week_seq nulls first`, **limits** to 100 rows.
[base] > 
[base] > The query runs in ~6s on DuckDB and returns the requested 100-row result set.
